==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Grenadine
<hw>Gren`a*dine"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A thin gauzelike fabric of silk or wool, for women's
wear.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A trade name for a dyestuff, consisting essentially
of impure fuchsine.</def></p>

<p><-- 3. a liqueur -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grenado</ent>⟦br⟧
